09/08: StatoilHydro has decided to bring forward repairs to its Kvitebjoern pipeline, with the operator now planning to carry out the work in the first quarter of 2009.  The pipeline was closed on August 20 following the discovery of a minor gas leak during a routine inspection following a scheduled shut-down. The leak is at the same point in the pipeline that was damaged by a ship's anchor in 2007. Following temporary repairs, the Kvitebjoern pipeline was qualified for short-term use in January 2008, pending permanent repairs that were initially scheduled for summer 2009. StatoilHydro has now reassessed various alternative solutions and plans to start the repairs to the pipeline at the turn of the year. It is not certain how long the repair work will take, but the operator expects production to resume by the end of the first quarter of 2009.
